With a scheduled appointment, I was hoping to be able to switch on the yoga early in the morning but it didn't happen, but as soon as I got home, I had the tv switched and ready to go and I am glad I did.  I always find I am put in a better frame of mind and having this one routine at the start of the day is beneficial too because I always feel better at the end.

Today didn't feel like anything we have done over the past two weeks and each day is always refreshing.  Yesterday, I started doing an at home resistance workout including squats and this morning, I am feeling the work out, so starting with the massage on the legs, was the best start to today's session, although I did not concentrate solely on the calf and ankle regions.  

I am finally getting to be in the present when I come to the mat, and listening to Adriene guide me through the session really puts me in a better place because I am tuned into what she is talking about and focusing on my actions on the mat and not caring about what is happening in my life at the moment.  I really liked the way the day started off with the cat/cow in a sitting position.  I found it to be a great way to start instead of being in a table top position.  

I found today's stretching really beneficial and I did find that over the short period of time, my thighs were not as sore as they were when I started the class for the day.  I am still not flexible but I do know I have good balance but for some unknown reason I wasn't well balanced when it came to today's leg work out.  Usually I am really well balanced and can stand up for awhile but today, something was a bit off.

As for tomorrow, I will be on the mat early and I look forward to the challenge ahead.

Another check-in, this week has actually been a little harder than the previous ones, which has helped with my hip alignment and when I'm walking around getting errands done I can tell my steps are more connected and balanced! I normally favor a bit on my left side and even when I sit in chairs I notice i always kinda lean on that left hip. I'm working on it and this week has been killer on my upper thighs and hips which is nice to have a bit more of a challenge and I notice my body is slowly starting to even out with each day. :D I'm still going hard at it and doing about 1.5 hours a day if I have the time. I love that whatever I might be struggling with, I can target those areas with your videos and work on that strength while still getting my daily video done as well. (I learned my lesson last time when I worked my core and abs last week at the gym then got home to do the daily video and that day was all abs as well. I was about screaming when I had to pulse up and reach for my toes. lol) Anyways, this was a long one. Hope everyone's sticking with it! Just a couple more weeks, you got it guys! :) Namaste! <3

Hi Adriene,
Dunno how much of your comments you get to read, but if you're reading this thank you so much. It goes on a bit longer than this, so if you want to stop now, that's okay!

I've been doing yoga with for quite a while now and at the beginning I was very frustrated (still am with some balancing poses!) and I wasn't practising self-care. I squeezed and manipulated my body into those positions. But now, I'm okay. It's sometimes frustrating if I can't get a posture, but I let myself do the 'easier' version (before I would head for the hard ones that were meant for more practiced yogis straight away!) 

So, all in all, I thought I'd really got this self care down.

But then you invited us to recognise our thoughts at the beginning. And I realised I'm STILL not practising self care. It's not early here - I started at 7amish - but I went out for about four hours yesterday. For most people, that would be nothing, but I suffer from pretty extreme anxiety and had a panic attack. Yet, dang it - I was gonna do my practice at the same time, course I was! What would have kinder to do to myself is stay in bed a little longer, read my book and recognise that I am worn out. It's a whole body thing.

So, I forgive myself for panicking at some school children yesterday. And I forgive myself for making the wrong call today. It's okay to get things wrong. This was a very moving practice to me.

Anyway, dunno if you're even reading this (!), but I hope that you get to read some of your comments, and just a thank you for helping me realise that self-care goes beyond the yoga mat. Although I really can't massage myself!

Much love,

Ellen

PS I'm getting the emails about each day's practice two days late - can this be changed? Or can one of our lovely group of Adrienes somehow email it to me on the right day? It's very frustrating. I dunno how that could happen without one of showing our email addresses... anyway, see what happens.

Namaste.
